definition: Western Sichuan
abbr. for Sichuan Province 四川[Si4 chuan1] in southwest China
river/creek/plain/an area of level country
the West/abbr. for Spain 西班牙[Xi1 ban1 ya2]/Spanish
west

sentences.english: Classical gardens in Western Sichuan have an old history and own unique characteristics.
sentences.chinese: 川西古典園林具有悠久的歷史和自身的獨特性。

sentences.english: The natural gas enrichment of Jurassic depression in the west of Sichuan is mainly controlled by lithofacies.
sentences.chinese: 川西坳陷侏羅系天然氣富集主要受巖相控制。

sentences.english: West Sichuan is region abundant in wildlife .
sentences.chinese: 川西是野生動物豐富的地區。

sentences.english: The Wanglang Preserve in western Sichuan is the haunt of the giant panda.
sentences.chinese: 川西的王朗自然保護區是大熊貓出沒的地方。

sentences.english: The West Sichuan depression and Central Sichuan uplift transitional zone in Sichuan Basin are slope zones.
sentences.chinese: 四川盆地川西坳陷與川中隆起過渡帶是一個斜坡地帶。

sentences.english: The second member of the Upper Triassic Xujiahe Formation is the regional gas horizons in the middle part of western Sichuan depression.
sentences.chinese: 須家河組二段是川西坳陷中的區域氣層。
